### F. Tagging & Versioning Images

```powershell
docker tag node-app-demo:1.0 node-app-demo:1.1
docker tag node-app-demo:1.0 yourusername/node-app-demo:1.0
```

**Recommended practices:**
- Adopt semantic versioning (`1.0.0`, `1.0.1`)
- Avoid depending on the `:latest` tag in production environments
- In CI pipelines, tag images with the Git commit SHA for traceability

---

### G. CMD vs ENTRYPOINT Explained

```dockerfile
# CMD — the default command, easily replaced at runtime
CMD ["node", "app.js"]

# ENTRYPOINT — the fixed executable for the container
ENTRYPOINT ["node", "app.js"]
CMD ["--port", "3001"]
```

```powershell
docker run myapp                    # runs entrypoint with default cmd args
docker run myapp --port 4000        # entrypoint runs with overridden args
```

